eNCA's senior reporter Aviwe Mtila filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 BLOEMFONTEIN - Eskom will take over the electricity distribution of one of its biggest debtors, the Maluti-a-Phofung Local Municipality in the Free State. It follows another oversight visit from Deputy President David Mabuza, who's looked into the water and electricity challenges in the area. READ: Eskom sells two buildings for R76m Maluti-a-Phofung Local Municipality owes the power utility over R5-billion. * eNCA's senior reporter Aviwe Mtila filed this report.